rvm ruby-1.8.7 do gem install -v 2.3.18 rails
rvm ruby-1.8.7 do gem install mysql 
rvm use 1.8.7
ruby -rubygems script/server -p8090

To see the logs from the web interface: 
in the splay controller configuration, be sure to have:
    LinkLogDir = "#{Dir.pwd}/links" -> LinkLogDir = "/log/"
ln -s splaweb/logs controller/link

If you host the splayweb on a VM behind the clusterinfo machine, you must turn ON port-forwarding on clusterinfo machine:
sudo iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -p tcp --dport 8090 -j DNAT --to 10.0.0.13:8090 
where:
-- 8090 is the port used when starting the splayweb
-- 10.0.0.13 is the machine hosting the splayweb application


To test with Ruby 2.0.0:
apply this patch:

Index: script/server
===================================================================
--- script/server	(revisione 1815)
+++ script/server	(copia locale)
@@ -1,3 +1,3 @@
 #!/usr/bin/env ruby
-require File.dirname(__FILE__) + '/../config/boot'
-require 'commands/server'
\ No newline at end of file
+require_relative '../config/boot'
+require 'commands/server'


Then, install required runtime and dependencies:
rvm install 2.0.0
rvm use 2.0.0
gem install rails -v 2.3.18
gem install iconv


